==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Neap
<hw>Neap</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. <er>Neb</er>,
<er>Nape</er>.]</ety> <def>The tongue or pole of a cart or other vehicle
drawn by two animals.</def> <mark>[U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Neap</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Neap
<hw>Neap</hw> <pr>(n⟦emac⟧p)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[As.
<ets>n⟦emac⟧p</ets>fl⟦omac⟧d neap flood; cf. <ets>hnipian</ets> to bend,
incline.]</ety> <def>Low.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Neap tides</b></col>, <cd>the lowest tides of the lunar
month, which occur in the second and fourth quarters of the moon; --
opposed to <contr>spring tides</contr>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Neap</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Neap
<hw>Neap</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A neap tide.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>High springs and dead <qex>neaps</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Harkwill.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

